chunk_content: Notably, infants may be >12 months of age at time of ART initiation and be included under PMTCT_HEI_POS_ART if the sample collection occurred at <12 months of age. The ART initiation disaggregate within HEI will allow us to report a linked infant ART initiation outcome for each positive infant reported. For more information, see 131 section on "How to review for data quality." Proxy Positivity: Proxy positivity is best calculated using age disaggregates (0-≤2 months and 2-12 T months) for PMTCT_HEI_POS, divided by the sum of PMTCT_HEI_POS + PMTCT_HEI_NEG using the E S same age disaggregates. Summing multiple quarters of data is recommended, as quarter-specific T comparisons may provide a less accurate proxy. I N G A rough proxy calculation for results returned: PMTCT_HEI_POS + PMTCT_HEI_NEG total numerator (results returned) can be compared with PMTCT_EID (samples collected) in the same quarter to understand the proportion of all samples collected that have been returned.
